We just thought it did too much for what we needed.  It&#x27;s a great library, and if I were parsing URLs in my apps I&#x27;d use it.  But we just wanted a single get() interface and support for complex objects in the URL.<p>Arg.js turns an object like this:<p><pre><code>    {
      tags: [&quot;one&quot;, &quot;two&quot;, &quot;three&quot;],
      deep: {
        nested: {
          objects: true
        }
      }
    }
</code></pre>
into this:<p><pre><code>    #?tags[0]=one&tags[1]=two&tags[2]=three&deep.nested.objects=true</code></pre>
